entries.meaning: A piece of protective gear meant to be inserted in the ear canal to protect the wearer's hearing from loud noises or the intrusion of water.

verbs.description: earplug (third-person singular simple present earplugs, present participle earplugging, simple past and past participle earplugged)

examples: In this same strain of mouse, earplugging from 17-22 days postpartum is effective in inducing susceptibility to audiogenic seizures...
